title: EDEN CONFIDENTIAL: Don't call me Yoko! David Furnish on the fight for control of Elton John's empire
description: RICHARD EDEN: He is the husband who caused acrimony when he took over the management of Sir Elton John's affairs, but David Furnish declares, Please don't call me Yoko.

title: Midwinter Ball rocked as Greens Senator Lidia Thorpe screams about fossil fuels
description: Lidia Thorpe, who was one of four Greens on the Midwinter Ball guest list, raised her fist and yelled about 'fossil fools' before joining a protest outside.

title: Choice issues warning about portable baby cots in Australia
description: Consumer advocacy group Choice tested dozens of portable baby cots and found that almost 70 per cent didn't meet Australian safety standards, including products from Kmart, Target and Baby Bunting.

title: Plan to send asylum seekers to Rwanda was made possible by Tony Blair, court hears
description: Leftie lawyers' fighting to stop the Government sending Channel migrants to Rwanda were told at the High Court yesterday that Tony Blair had made the scheme possible.

title: Liz Truss warns staff to smarten up as she turns her back on the Dominic Cummings-style outfits
description: Newly elected Prime Minister Liz Truss has warned scruffy dressers will need to smarten up, as she looks to distance her image from her predecessor.

title: Meriton founder Harry Triguboff blasts Sydney's 'problem' with apartments as he develops Queensland
description: One of Australia's richest men has joined a chorus of property developers and CEOs in slamming Sydney's 'big problem' with gaining approvals for new builds.

title: Nationals leader David Littleproud and girlfriend Amelia Dobson's awkward Midwinter Ball mistake
description: Nationals leader David Littleproud and his girlfriend Amelia Dobson were the victims on an awkward table list error at the Midwinter Ball at Parliament House.

title: More than 200 passengers are escorted off a Qantas flight under police guard
description: Passengers onboard a Qantas flight to Melbourne were led under heavy police guard to be re-screened by security upon arrival after a passenger made it onboard without being chcked.

title: Therese Coffey is the Health Secretary who admits cheerfully admits that she is no role model
description: Miss Coffey, 50, who is also Deputy Prime Minister, told host Nick Ferrari: 'I've just realised my alarm is going off on my phone - you're getting a bit of Dr Dre. It's just an 8 o'clock alarm. Sorry.'

title: Jesus Christ was world's first cricketer, experts claim
description: Details of The Second Coming's cricket playing days as a child were apparently found in a previously unseen Gospel.

title: Anger as Foreign Office 'likes' tweet that branded Priti Patel 'unspeakably cruel'
description: Supporters of former Home Secretary Priti Patel (pictured) yesterday protested after a Foreign Office Twitter account 'liked' a tweet calling her 'unspeakably cruel'

title: EPHRAIM HARDCASTLE: Are Boris and Carrie headed for Chipping Norton?
description: EPHRAIM HARDCASTLE: Are Boris and Carrie soon to join David Cameron and Jeremy Clarkson in the Chipping Norton set?

title: Mel C reveals how the pressures of global fame led to depression
description: JAN MOIR: Mel C's rather bleak tale of female pop stardom is dominated by clinical depression and an eating disorder that almost took her to the point of suicide.

title: Hilarious moment SUV spotted on Florida highway with a MONSTER 11-foot gator strapped to tailgate
description: The bizarre image posted to social media appears to show an alligator strapped to the tailgate of an SUV in Brevard County. The gator was likely hunted as part of hunting season which runs until November.

title: Australian bikies who quit gang life reveal how they're targeted, attacked, robbed and can't sleep
description: Ex bikies have spoken about the fear of being targeted when they leave a gang, unable to sleep and facing violent retribution. One ex bikie says he still sleeps with one eye open.

title: British humanitarian worker suffered 'possible unspeakable torture' and was missing body parts
description: Paul Urey's body was returned to Ukraine after suffering 'possible unspeakable torture.' Officials allege his corpse had sustained multiple cuts and was missing body parts.

title: More than 1,400 runners will finish murdered billionaire heiress Eliza Fletcher's jogging route
description: A group of Memphis women are arranging a run on Friday morning past the spot where Eliza Fletcher was abducted while jogging, to demand that women be safe to run any time.

title: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: A fine start, but now the real work begins
description: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: If Liz Truss suffered from nerves during her first Commons Question Time as Prime Minister, she certainly didn't show it.
